history.content: Hi! I took 16A in the fall. From what I remember, you sign up for the 999 disc section and the lab time that you desire (looks like you did both). Did you choose an open lab section? If you did, you should wait like ~6 hours - I read somewhere that the waitlist processes every 6 hours or so (I also had to wait a couple of hours before getting off the waitlist in the fall and I chose an open lab section). Hopefully this helped!

If you successfully enrolled in EECS16a this semester, please help me out

I just enrolled but I'm not sure if I did it right...? Is 16a using 999 sections then assigning actual discussion times after the class starts (I know many classes do this), or using the CalCentral enrollment tool to pick sections? I'm confused because on the 16a page in the class schedule, it lists both a 999 disc section and a bunch of discussion sections at different times.

I first tried enrolling using the class number (28998) which led to being asked to select a discussion and lab. All of the disc sections were closed except one with the yellow waitlist triangle (205), but on the class schedule page, I saw that this section had negative open seats.

So I decided instead to try to enroll using the class number associated with the 999 section, and it only asked me to pick a lab section then I was able to enroll. I was still placed on the waitlist (LEC #19) and I'm not sure why, since the class has open seats and the lab section I selected has open seats. Overall I'm just really confused about how discussion sections work for this class, and whether I made a mistake in the way I enrolled. Any advice would be amazing!
history.subject: EECS16A enrollment issues, confused about discussion sections
